⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Lebannen (Arren)
node U1 · U1 · ⟦Lebannen (Arren):U1:7f03b8⟧

WHO   — Lebannen (Arren) — the King who walked the dry land
WHAT  — The heir who walked the dry land of the dead beside the Archmage, faced the unmaking of magic, and returned to unite the Archipelago as its first king in centuries.
WHERE — U1 · Le Guin  Framework inputs: Earthsea  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because a world drained of meaning needs one who will accept death so that life may keep its worth; because kingship is service, not dominion, and the crown is carried, not seized.
HOW   — By unwavering loyalty to Ged, by crossing the wall of stones into the dry land and climbing the Mountain of Pain, by drinking from the spring of life — and by learning that to be king is to give, not to take.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  Only in dying life — and the crown is not a thing you take, but a weight you choose to carry.

spoken token : gro-stath-vek   ·   hex : 7f03b8
